|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|                                   0.051.900                                  |
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|

|==============================================================================|
|                              APPLICATION CHANGES                             |
|==============================================================================|

* Reworked how the renderer selects (and uses) colors to highlight nicknames,
  if that option is turned on.
* Bugfix: the nickname display (showing who is "saying" a line of chat) had its
  color set to the custom color even if "highlight nicks in chat" option was
  turned off.
* Bugfix: the username input widget on the connect dialog was forbidding input
  that includes the "/" character, which is needed for some bouncers.
* Bugfix: server passwords were being saved "incorrectly" in the connection
  history.
* Bugfix: the SASL interface now updates correctly in the connection dialog.
* The "connect" button on the connection dialog is now disabled if the hostname,
  port, nickname, username, or realname inputs are empty.

|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|                                   0.051.850                                  |
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|

|==============================================================================|
|                              APPLICATION CHANGES                             |
|==============================================================================|

* Bugfix: fixed a bug in automatic hostmask fetching.
* New feature: hide certain system messages from view in channels. Each channel
  now has an option in the chat's right click menu to hide JOIN, PART, QUIT,
  NICK, MODE, and TOPIC messages from view. The option is stored in the config
  file, along with the channel's name and network. The option to hide all these
  messages from view in ALL channels remains in the settings, but this gives
  users fine control over specific channels.
* Bugfix: sometimes, initial messages to the client could cause an error that
  would cause them not to display.
* The "highlight nick in chat" feature has been changed to allow users to set
  custom colors for specific users. Colors are stored by network with
  hostmasks, so the individual nickname is not as important. The MERK user's
  nickname will be highlighted using the current text style settings.
* Added an option to the chat right click menus to reload (rerender) the chat
  display.
* Added a new "color" icon, for the userlist right click menu to set colors.
* Added a "highlight nicks in chat" toggle to the "Display" submenu in the
  "Settings" menu.
* Changed how "away" and "back" statuses are shown in userlists. Users that are
  "away" and now shown in the selected user color (if they have one); their
  nick is shown in normal weight (not bold) and italics.
* New option: show/hide user colors in userlists. If both "show colors in
  userlists" and "use colors in chat" are turned off, the option to set or
  remove colors is removed from the userlist context menu. The new settings has
  been added to the "settings" dialog.
* Bugfix: it was possible to "ignore" yourself from the userlist context menu.
  This option has been removed.
* The "/window layout" command no longer specifies a port in the hostID for
  each window in the generated script.
* Bugfix: the hotkey manager would occasionally throw an error and delete an
  edited hotkey after editing.
* Nicknames without a color assigned to them are now also highlighted in chat,
  if that option is turned on.
* If nickname highlighting in chat is turned on, chatlogs in channel windows
  will rerender after a short period of time to show previously logged chat
  with the chosen colors. This can be turned off with a settings in the config
  file with the /config command or by editing the configuration file, or in the
  "settings" dialog.
* Added an option to sort the entries in the windowbar. Entries can be set in
  order of subwindow creation (the default), reverse subwindow creation order,
  alphabetically, or reverse alphabetically.
* Windowbar entry sorting can now be changed via the "settings" dialog, the
  windowbar's right click menu, or the /config command.
* Bugfix: removed an unused icon from the resource file.
* Added a new icon (in both light and dark mode) for windowbar sorting.
* Bugfix: windowbar entry sorting could end up wrong in some rare instances.
  If the number of window entries was very large, full window entries and icon
  only window entries were sorted seperately. Now, the full list is sorted
  properly.
* New options: show the user's nickname in the set style color or underlined
  (or both) in userlists. Both of these options are off by default.
* New option: users can now set a minimum nickname length for highlighting in
  channel chat (so that users with single or double character nicks consisting
  of very common letters don't end up being highlighted constantly). The
  minimum is set to 0 (zero) by default, so ALL nicknames will be highlighted.
* Bugfix: the "unsimplified" text on the log manager rendered very oddly when
  the log manager subwindow was maximized. The text has been removed from the
  dialog.
* Bugfix: automatic rerendering could fail on occasion. This has been fixed.
* The settings dialog now hides itself while applying settings.
* Added an option to hide the subwindow to the right click context menu of
  channels and private message windows.
* Bugfix: the "message filter" menu was shown in the right click menu of
  private message windows. It no longer is.
* Bugfix: logs would be saved on window close whether anything had been added
  to or not. Now, logs are only saved if there's something new to save.
* Bugfix: user colors are now properly loaded for chat rerendering.
* Bugfix: if the "always show active window first" option in the windowbar is
  turned on, the active window will always be shown first, regardless of how
  the windowbar is sorted.
* Removed an unused icon from the resource file.
* Changed the "console" icon to something that looks a little better, and makes
  more sense.
* Bugfix: fixed a crashing bug with the renderer in the log manager.
* Added "View" to the log viewer tab title in the log manager.
* Re-arranged the userlist context menu.
* New command: "/reload", which forces a window to re-render their chat log.
* New subcommand for "/window": "reload", which forces ALL chat windows to
  rerender their chat logs.
* Bugfix: some plugin events related to SASL login could crash the client or
  not execute if certain errors occured.
* Removed the IRCv3 capability request (and handling) for account-notify.
* Added an option to notify the user when a CTCP request is received. This
  option is turned off by default. It can be turned on in the "settings" dialog
  on the "messages" page.
* Bugfix: when initially spawning subwindows, MERK would unneccesarily re-
  render text multiple times (once when a style was applied, and once when a
  log was loaded). This slowed the client down a bit. This no longer occurs.
* Bugfix: adding or removing words from the internal dictionary will no longer
  crash the client.

|==============================================================================|
|                              PLUGIN API CHANGES                              |
|==============================================================================|

* New inherited method: "request". This allows plugins to force MERK to request
  specific IRCv3 extensions from servers on connection.
* New event: "nak", which triggers when an IRC server DOESN'T support a
  request()ed IRCv3 extension.
* New event: "ack", which triggers when an IRC server DOES support a request()-
  ed IRCv3 extension.

|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|                                   0.051.800                                  |
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|

|==============================================================================|
|                              APPLICATION CHANGES                             |
|==============================================================================|

* Hotkey commenting in the script and Python editors now places the comment
  symbol or command at the beginning of every selected line, no matter how much
  of the line is selected.
* Bugfix: the script editor now uses the command issue symbol ('/' by default)
  and the alias interpolation symbol ('$' by default) set in the configuration
  file, rather than the raw, default symbols, for comment generation and alias
  insertion.
* Added an option to the editors' context menu to insert the name of a
  currently open private chat.
* Added options to insert calls to "/script" and "insert" to the context menu
  of the script editor.
* Added subwindow snapping; when subwindows get close to each other, they will
  "snap" together. This behavior can be toggled on and off, and the distance
  that windows need to be in order to snap (within 20 pixels) can be changed.
  By default, this behavior is turned on.
* Added subwindow snapping to the settings dialog.
* Added a new "Subwindow" submenu to the "Settings" menu.
* Removed some connection dialog settings from the "Connections" subwindow in
  the "Settings" menu.
* Added subwindow order setting to the "Subwindow" submenu in the "Settings"
  menu.
* Bugfix: text pasted into a script or Python editor now strips any existing
  formatting.
* Removed the option to toggle line numbers in the connection dialog. Now, they
  are always shown.
* Bugfix: syntax highlighting for comments in the script editor no longer
  leaves strings, aliases, etc, in their highlighting color when commented.
* Trying (and failing) to read a file with the script-only "read" command will
  now behave as if the file is empty, and return "*".
* New script-only command: "write", which allows scripts to write text to
  files.
* New script-only command: "getfile", which shows an "open file" dialog, and
  stores the result in an alias.
* New script-only command: "setfile", which shows an "save file" dialog, and
  stores the result in an alias.
* Bugfix: macro command was being parsed incorrectly.
* Bugfix: unmacro command was being parsed incorrectly.
* Changed /folder command to only open one directory at a time.
* New option: chat input that starts with the "issue command" symbol, and isn't
  followed by a valid command, will not be sent to the server as chat. If the
  user wants to send a chat message that starts with the "issue command"
  symbol, they have to add it twice, which "escapes" the "issue command"
  symbol.
* Bugfix: fixed a bug with subwindow snapping. Subwindows will no longer
  attempt to "snap" to the parent window edges, and will explicitly ignore the
  windowbar and menubar.
* Bugfix: subwindows now check whether they're being dragged more efficiently.
* New script-only command: "append", which appends text to a file. "write" no
  longer appends to a file, but overwrites it.
* Re-wrote how blocking scripting commands work; now, almost all dialog events
  are routed through a single qtsignal rather than 5 (or more) of them.
* The "context" script-only command can now take a hostID as an argument to
  specify why server a targeted window should be connected to.
* The pre-command error check on scripts has been expanded to include the
  context command.
* New built-in alias: $_CONNECTED, which contains a list of all of the hostIDs
  that MERK is connected to, seperated by spaces.
* The "input" and "number" script only commands now use the Qt built-in dialog
  functions instead of custom dialogs.
* New script-only command: "decimal", which requests a decimal number from the
  user, much like how "number" works.
* Bugfix: closing the script/Python editor could occasionally crash the client.
* The "number" and "decimal" script-only commands have been changed to "return"
  * (instead of 0) if the command's dialog is canceled.
* Removed the "/msgbox" command, and made it a script-only command named
  "msgbox". The command can still be called from the "if" command.
* Bugfix: the error checking for scripts, specifically with the "if" command,
  is now checking for errors properly.
* MERK has a new logo and icon! Thanks to the folks in #lobby on TheMansion
  IRC network for all the help.
* Bugfix: there coule be errors in tokenizing arguments to the "/call" command.
* Bugfix: there coule be errors in tokenizing arguments to the "/script"
  command.
* Bugfix: the script-only command "insert" could improperly tokenize arguments,
  and didn't handle errors in inserted files properly.
* Bugfix: the "context" command would error out if "*" was used as a window
  name (to reference a server window). This argument is not needed (as using
  "context" with a hostID or the name of the window will switch to the server
  window), but since that's an option with many other commands, I wanted to
  make sure that an error wasn't thrown.
* New option: set an image as the background for subwindows. Just like with the
  MDI area, only for the "texture" of the subwindow itself.
* Removed non-input related options from the "three-dot" input menu button.
* Completely revamped the "three-dot" input menu button, and added new options
  to toggle markdown, IRC color input, emojis, and ASCIImojis.
* Revamped chat and server log right click menus.

|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|                                   0.051.750                                  |
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|

|==============================================================================|
|                              APPLICATION CHANGES                             |
|==============================================================================|

* Nicknames are in bold, and full IRC color/formatting is viewable in the log
  viewer.
* CTCP ACTIONs are now in bold and italics in the log viewer. "Human readable"
  log exports no longer display CTCP ACTIONs as chat.
* The log viewer now notifies the user when it takes a little while to load/
  render a log, in the window status bar.
* Bugfix: system/server messages are now rendered properly in the log viewer
  and in "human readable" exports, as are notices and private messages.
* The log viewer now can toggle UNIX epoch time in "human readable" output.
* The script and Python editor now feature a line number display.
* Bugfix: line numbers in the editors now update properly.
* Bugfix: the script/Python editor now updates the "changed" status properly.
* Bugfix: the script/Python editor no longer starts up in the "changed" state
  the first time it is launched in a session.
* Added an option to add line numbers to the connection script editor in the
  connection dialog (it's turned off by default).
* The current line is "highlighted" in the script/Python editor. The color of
  the line highlight is either darker than the background color (if the color
  if light) or lighter (if the color is dark).
* Added an option to toggle line highlighting in the editor. This feature is
  turned off by default.
* Added an option to save (and restore) the main application window location.
* Join, part, quit, mode, topic, and nick messages can now be "hidden" in
  channel chats. They will still be logged (if that option is turned on), and
  the display of them can be toggled on and off.
* Removed the "View" title from the log manager log viewer tab, and replaced
  it with a magnifying glass icon.
* Added a "callable method" generator to the Python editor.
* Untitled MERK and Python scripts are now differentiated in the windowbar.
* Bugfix: Calling /config import or /config export (with no additional
  arguments) could crash MERK if called from a script.
* The "message" script-only command has been removed. The /msgbox command is
  now blocking if called from a script. The /msgbox command can also be called
  as the result as a successful "if" call, like any other non-script-only
  command.
* The "halt" script-only command can now be issued from the "if" command.
* "Strings" (that is, text contained in single or double quotes) are now
  highlighted in the script editor.
* Bugfix: MERK could crash when random was used with an alias that was
  previously created and used prior.
* The "read" script-only command is now blocking.
* Removed the option to control whether script-created aliases are deleted when
  a script ends. Aliases are now always deleted, no matter what.
* As all aliases are now deleted on script end, calling /unalias in a script
  does absolutely nothing. Calling /unalias will produce an error that prevents
  a script from executing.
* Bugfix: MERK searched for script files improperly.
* Added channel scripts. MERK can be configured to execute a script when the
  client joins a channel. The script is "bound" to the channel's network, so
  the script is executed no matter what server the client connects to.
* Two arguments are now passed to channel scripts: the name of the channel, and
  the hostID of the server the channel is connected to.
* Added a built-in alias: $_GLOBAL, which is set to "1" if the global script
  exists and has been executed, and "0" if the global script doesn't exist or
  hasn't been executed.
* New script-only command: "hostmask". This command retrieves a hostmask for
  a nickname and stores it in an alias. If the hostmask is not known or is not
  found, the alias is set to "*".
* Made some scripting error messages a bit clearer.
* If a file being read by the "read" command is empty or contains only
  whitespace, the alias will be set to "*".
* Bugfix: the syntax highlighter in the Python editor now correctly highlights
  the .script method.
* Added a new "contributors" tab to the "about" dialog, and added robotmachine
  and BreadcrumbPattie to it.
* New script-only command: "escape". This command escapes MERK markdown in text
  and stores the result in an alias.
* Links are now clickable in the log manager viewer.
* Cleaned up the connection dialog layout.
* Bugfix: if MERK is launched without connecting to anything, and then the
  script or Python editor is launched, the document was always marked as
  "changed", even if the user didn't change anything. This no longer happens.
* Added an option to the editor context menu to "comment" or "uncomment"
  selected text. This is a toggle, with a new hotkey (Ctrl+/). This works in
  both script and Python mode.
* Added an option to insert built-in aliases to the context menu in the script
  editor.
* Added an option to find/find and replace to the context menu in the script
  editor.
* Bugfix: leading/trailing backticks are now ignored in URLs when rendering
  URLs as links in chat.
* Removed the emoji shortcode list PDF from the app, and replaced it with a
  link to the library's shortcode website.
* Added a new menu icon to the app resources.

|==============================================================================|
|                              PLUGIN API CHANGES                              |
|==============================================================================|

* Bugfix: the plugin inherited method "script" could crash the app, mostly due
  to the fact that the API could occasionally attempt to run the script on the
  server window's QMDIArea subwindow rather than the server window's widget.
  This has been fixed.

|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|                                   0.051.700                                  |
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|

|==============================================================================|
|                              APPLICATION CHANGES                             |
|==============================================================================|

* Changed the default username (if the user has not entered one) to the
  application name, as set by the config.
* The global alias table is now updated in realtime as scripts run.
* Added an option to the config file and the settings dialog to toggle whether
  to delete aliases created in scripts at script end.
* Added a menu option to both the script and Python editor to open a new blank
  editor window, in whatever mode required.
* Hotkey key sequences are now styled like aliases in the script editor's
  syntax highlighting.
* Updated the README (both the HTML file bundled with the app and the README
  markdown in the repo).
* Two new script-only commands: "loop" (which takes a single numerical argument,
  the number of times to repeat the loop, and starts a looping block), and
  "pool" (which ends a looping block).
* In the first "error checking" pass before script execution, the first script-
  stopping error will be displayed rather than the last one.
* Targets created with the "target" command are now case-insensitive.
* MERK now supports logging into server accounts with SASL. Account information
  is saved directly to the user configuration, and will be used in the future
  if the data is present.
* Added an option to disconnect on SASL authentication failure (turned on by
  default). If prompting for a new server on a lost connection is turned on,
  then the user will be prompted for a new server; if not, a message box is
  displayed letting the user know of the failure.
* The /user command now has a subcommand ("sasl") that can add and remove SASL
  accounts from the user configuration file. Call "/user sasl" to list all SASL
  accounts. Call "/user sasl add" to add an SASL account, "/user sasl
  remove" to remove one, and "/user sasl edit" to edit one.
* Bugfix: dialog text entries for server port numbers now limit input to
  positive integers only.
* Added the option to toggle password visibility in the "join channel" dialog
  and the SASL account entry dialog.
* If we can get the server to send hostmasks with NAMES replies, then we don't
  have to do mass whois on channel users. We now check the server capabilities
  to make sure that's what's happening. If the server sends hostmasks in NAME
  replies, the "request hostmasks on channel join" option is now "ignored".
* MERK now handles IRCv3 capabilities better.
* Added a link explaining "Levenshtein_distance" to the "Spellcheck" section of
  the "Settings" dialog.
* Tweaks to the "Settings" dialog.
* Added IRCv3 capabilities to the "server information" menu.
* Bugfix: "blank" passwords are no longer sent during the connection process.
* Users can now create a "global script" by creating a script named
  "global.merk" in the "scripts" directory. This script will be executed when
  MERK connects to the first server in a session, in the context of that
  connection's server window. All commands (including script-only commands) are
  available for use in "global.merk", only aliases created in the script are
  NOT destroyed on the script's completion.
* Added an option to set the filename of the "global" script to the
  configuration file. This can be set/changed with the "/config" command.
* Two arguments are now passed to the "global" script: the host and port of the
  server being connected to.
* New script-only command: "input". This gets input from the user in a dialog,
  and stores the input in an alias. If the user doesn't input anything or
  cancels the dialog, the alias is set to "*". This command is blocking, and
  will pause execution of the script until the dialog is closed.
* Bugfix: setting "loop" with a count of 0 (zero) would result in an "eternal"
  loop. Now, loops with a count of 0 only execute once.
* New script-only command: "number". This gets a number in a range from the
  user and stores it in an alias. If the user cancels the dialog, the alias is
  set to 0 (zero).
* New script-only command: "message". This displays a blocking messagebox to
  the user with a short message.
* Removed a lot of dialogs from the source code. The script editor no longer
  has "command generators", as the scripting language is getting complex
  enough that users should really read the documentation to write scripts.
* Added a new example script to the documentation.
* Bugfix: calling "if" could crash the client in some circumstances.
* Changes to "halt": calling "halt" now brings up a blocking dialog that asks
  the user if they want to halt script execution. If the user presses "cancel",
  the script will continue execution.
* Updated the MERK User Guide with all new features, and some better
  explanations of concepts.
* The log manager can now export IRC logs to a "human readable" format that is
  closer to "traditional" IRC logs, with a human readable date/time, followed
  by the user's nickname, ": ", and the user's chat. IRC colors/formatting are
  stripped from chat.
* The log manager now offers a log viewer. In the viewer, logs are stripped of
  timestamps, hostmasks, and IRC colors/formatting.
* Single clicking on a log entry in the list now loads a log in the log
  manager, now.
* SASL authentication now makes sure that the server supports the PLAIN
  mechanism before sending the username/password for login. If the server
  doesn't support PLAIN, MERK will not try to login.
* Bugfix: SASL authentication fails would not always close the file used with
  the "write all input/output to file" option. Now, the file is closed properly
  and when the "connection lost" trigger is triggered, whether the file is
  closed properly if checked.
* Search has be re-added to the log manager, and the log viewer is now the
  default visible tab.
* Tweaked how "hostmask harvesting" works: MERK will now more accurately grab
  hostmasks from messages, and try to not send as many WHOIS requests to the
  server.
* The default option to include server windows in the windowbar has been
  changed to "true". This will only have an effect on new installations.
* Bugfix: empty strings we sometimes added to the script argument list,
  breaking the "usage" command. "Empty" arguments are now removed from the
  arguments passed to a script (because it shouldn't be possible, with the way
  that scripts work).
* Bugfix: the windowbar now looks "good" (and is usable) when floating.
* Bugfix: the windowbar now rebuilds itself properly when it is docked.

|==============================================================================|
|                              PLUGIN API CHANGES                              |
|==============================================================================|

* SASL authentication fails now trigger the "error" event in plugins.

|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|                                   0.051.650                                  |
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|

|==============================================================================|
|                              APPLICATION CHANGES                             |
|==============================================================================|

* Bugfix: targets weren't being properly parsed when used with if...goto.
* Calling goto with a target that doesn't exist now shows an error message that
  states that.
* The /window layout command now includes settings for the main application 
  window. Hidden subwindows are now included, and explicitly hidden in the
  generated script.
* Bugfix: if aliases are disabled, random occasionally reported the wrong
  command name in error messages.
* New script-only command: read. This command reads in a text file and stores
  its contents in an alias. If a binary file is attempted to be used with this
  command, an error is shown.
* New built-in alias: $_DONATE. This contains the URL to donate to MERK's
  development.
* Bugfix: one of the checkboxes in the Settings dialog was not put into the
  layout correctly. This has been fixed.
* The font size of the Settings dialog is now fixed at 10pt, by default. The
  fixed size can be changed in the configuration file or with the /config
  command by changing the settings_dialog_font_size setting.
* Bugfix: changing application fonts did not always set all fonts on subwindows
  properly. This has been fixed.
* The "Save" menu option in the editors is now always enabled; if there is not
  a filename to save to, the "save as" dialog will be used.
* Bugfix: the "is this valid place to move a subwindow" function would
  occasionally say a location was invalid on large desktops or multiple screens.
  This has been fixed.
* Changed the name of the /window subcommand "resize" to "size", to more
  closely match the /size command.
* Scripts that call /alias when /alias is disabled will now display an error
  and not execute at all.
* Bugfix: random, read, and goto now display an error if they are called with
  the wrong number of arguments.
* Scripts that contain "if", "insert", and "goto" will no longer run at all if
  these commands are disabled.
* Bugfix: several script-only commands did not necessarily interpolate their
  inputs against the alias table. These commands have been "fixed": random,
  write, and halt.
* Bugfix: /print (and /prints) would occasionally repeat the second word in a
  message. This has been fixed.
* Script comments are now highlighted in the editor.
* Changed the build system. MERK now uses a "universal" major and minor version
  for building, rather than seperate versions for each platform.
* Scripts with a goto call with too many arguments (more than one) will no
  longer execute.
* Added an option to en/disable the "read" script-only command.
* Scripts that call "random" or "read" improperly will now no longer execute.
  Also, if aliases are disabled, scripts that contain these commands will no
  longer execute.
* Added a new plugin example to both the documentation and the repo.
* Added new tips to the "tips and tricks" dialog.
* Nickname autocomplete can now autocomplete all nicknames that are "visible"
  to the client. Nicknames in the current channel are given priority and will
  be completed first.
* New option: highlight nicknames from any channel that the client is present
  in in the text input widget. The option is turned off by default.
* New Flatpak distribution for Linux!
* Bugfix: fixed a race condition in the "read" command.
* Bugfix: Aliases in scripts did not have input values interpolated properly.
* Bugfix: /alias could throw "not in scope" errors in long running scripts
  improperly.
* Bugfix: /alias can now be reliably called from "if" commands without causing
  "not in scope" errors.
* Bugfix: calling a script-only command (besides "goto") as the result of a
  successful "if" call now prevents a script from executing and displays an
  error.
* Bugfix: if "goto" is disabled, calling "target" will show an error and
  prevent a script from executing.
* The syntax highlighter in the script editor now highlights non-script-only
  commands that appear anywhere on a line, not just at the beginning. Script-
  only commands are still only highlighted if they appear at the beginning of
  a line.
* New command: /warn works exactly like /print and /prints, and displays an
  error message in a window.
* If input syntax highlighting is turned on, hostIDs are now highlighted.
* Bugfix: commands like /print, /warn, etc., could not properly find windows
  by using the server's reported hostname. I discovered this when trying to
  print to a window on Freenode (which reports *.freenode.net as the host) and
  the commands did not find the appropriate window. This has been fixed.
* New "if" operator: (nin). Statement is true if the first argument is NOT
  contained in the second argument (basically, the opposite of "(in)").
* The /edit command can now create new connection scripts for a given hostID.
* When editing an alias with the /alias command, MERK now makes sure that the
  alias exists in the "right" scope before allowing the edit. For example,
  aliases created in scripts can only be edited in scripts, and aliases edited
  via the text input widget can only be edited via the text input widget.
* The /away and /back commands can now take a server as an optional argument,
  so that the "away" and "back" status can be set on other servers from windows
  that don't share the same context.
* /quote can now also take a server as an optional argument, much like /away
  and /back.
* Changed the way that messages are sent to the server. MERK now has overloaded
  the Twisted IRC client methods msg(), notice(), and describe() so that ANY
  messages sent via these methods (including from plugins when they use the
  Twisted client manually) will appear in the client's display without having
  to do it manually (which is how MERK worked before).
* Bugfix: outgoing notices are now written to the server window by default.
* Bugfix: private message are now being written to the server window properly.
* Bugfix: CTCP ACTION messages, when sent to private chats, are now written to
  server windows properly.
* Removed the /focus command, and moved the functionality to /show.
* Slightly changed how /window layout works; after all subwindows are set up,
  the generated script now sets focus on the window that called the command,
  but only if that window is visible.
* Bugfix: calling /delay could crash the client in certain circumstances.
* Bugfix: commands with subcommands (like /window) now have their subcommands
  highlighted properly if syntax highlighting in the text input widget is
  turned on.
* Bugfix: outgoing notices that contain CTCP messages (which are normally
  unable to be sent manually with MERK) are no longer displayed in the server
  window.
* Bugfix: messages over 400 characters (by default) are now displayed
  correctly, as they will appear to other users on the server, rather than as
  a single "chunk".

|==============================================================================|
|                              PLUGIN API CHANGES                              |
|==============================================================================|

* Changed the name of the Plugin inherited method resize() to size().
* Changed the Window class method size() to work exactly like the Plugin
  inherited method, and removed the Window class method resize().
* Changed the Console class method size() to work exactly like the Plugin
  inherited method, and removed the Console class method resize().
* The Window class methods message(), action(), and notice() no longer return
  booleans, as they are no longer needed.

|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|                                   0.051.600                                  |
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|

|==============================================================================|
|                              APPLICATION CHANGES                             |
|==============================================================================|

* New command: /fade. This sets the transparency of a chat subwindow by
  percentage, from 1 to 100. Call without any arguments to see the current
  subwindow's transparency.
* Modified the "/window layout" command to use /fade in the output.
* New option: the user's nickname is highlighted in chat using the same color
  scheme that's used to display the user's nickname as a speaker. This only
  happens in chat, and only when other's "speak" the user's nickname. Changing
  the user's nickname re-renders the chat to make sure the proper nick is
  highlighted. This can be en/disabled in the Settings dialog or with the
  /config command.
* Tweaked the connection dialog. "Flattened" the layout, and re-arranged some
  stuff. Removed a style sheet from the QTabWidget, which hopefull fixes a bug
  on some machines using dark mode.
* Bugfix: hitting ctrl+c when the connection dialog now exits properly, and
  doesn't throw an error.
* Bugfix: the "host" line entry on the connection dialog is now given focus at
  the launch of the connection dialog. If the "nickname" still needs to be
  entered, that widget is given focus.
* Revamped the channel list window. IRC formatting codes are now stripped from
  channel topics before display, and the "word wrap" option for channel entries
  has been removed.
* Bugfix: the "nickname is too long" error is now suppressed if the "show all
  server errors" option is not turned on. The client handles this error auto-
  matically.
* Bugfix: IRC color rendering no longer sets erroneous background or foreground
  colors.
* The function to convert IRC color and formatting codes into HTML is now
  "universalized", and available to every module in the project.
* The "working" cursor is now shows when creating/compiling the channel list
  dialog.
* Added the /fade command to the script editor's code generators.
* Bugfix?: delayed the execution of /list's functionality by 10 milliseconds so
  that the text input widget is cleared before the generation of the channel
  list dialog. Without this, the application looks "locked up" for a few
  seconds.
* Bugfix?: delayed displaying the output of the /config command when it's
  displaying all config values by 10 milliseconds, just like with the /list
  command, so the app doesn't appear to be locking up.
* Bugfix?: delayed the search/output of the /find and /window log commands.
* Moved the "search install directory" setting to the "Advanced" page in
  settings.
* Bugfix: the "en/disable text style editor" setting in the Settings dialog
  encouraged an unnecessary reboot when toggled.
* Selecting a server in the dropdown on the connect dialog now moves the cursor
  and focus to the "host" text input widget as soon as a server is selected.
* Bugfix: the menubar no longer looks misshappen when selecting a menu while
  using dark mode.
* New option: added servers to autocomplete. It only autocompletes servers that
  are actively connected (and registered). It uses the "hostid", which is
  accepted as a server name by most commands (the host and port used to connect
  to the server, separated by a ":").
* Added "hostids" to the syntax highlighting in the script editor. The
  "Highlighting" page has been updated; "hostids" use the same highlighting as
  channels.
* Bugfix: the /connectssl and /xconnectssl used "6667" for the default port,
  rather than "6697". This has been fixed.
* All the /connect commands can now take a single argument consisting of a
  "hostid", in the format "host:port:password". If port is left out, then
  the default port is used; if password is left out, a password is not used.
  The password can contain spaces.
* Added an option to automatically "refresh" the server channel list at an
  interval. By default, this option is turned off, and set to automatically
  refresh the channel list every 2 hours.
* Changed the /list command: if automatic channel refresh is turned off, and
  the channel list is "stale" (older than the automatic refresh time, default
  2 hours), a "fresh" channel list will be fetched from the server.
* Bugfix: some networks/servers (EFnet) don't send the "erroneous nickname"
  error when someone tries to register with a nickname that is longer than 9
  characters. Apparently, some servers just try to truncate the name down to 9
  characters, which can cause problems in the truncated nickname is already
  claimed. MERK now has a workaround for that.
* Bugfix: if the erroneous nickname setting is longer than 8 characters, it is
  reset to "Guest". This is noted in the documentation. The erroneous nickname
  is padded out to 9 characters with random numbers so we avoid nickname
  collisions.
* Bugfix: the /user and /nick commands now check for valid nicknames before
  they are sent to the server.
* The "erroneous nickname" fallback can now be edited in the Settings dialog.
* The use of the "erroneous nickname" fallback is now notified to the user
  in the server window.
* "Illegal" characters can no longer be put into text inputs for nicknames
  and usernames. These follow all the rules set forth in the IRC RFCs. Commands
  that work with nicknames (like /nick and /user) also follow these rules, and
  will not let users try to use "illegal" nicknames.
* Added an option to toggle "illegal" nickname input. The new option is added
  to the "Advanced" page in the Settings dialog. This option is turned on by
  default.
* Added a setting to the configuration file to control when to start trying to
  use the "erroneous nickname" fallback. This is set to "3" nick attempts, by
  default. The only way to change this setting is by manually editing the
  config file or by using the /config command.
* Bugfix: fixed a possible nickname collision race condition when using the
  "erroneous nickname" fallback during registration.
* Bugfix: the "page selector" widget in the Settings dialog's width is now set
  to a fixed width (taking the font and icon size into account). This should
  fix the bug where sometimes the width of he "page selector" would get out of
  whack with larger font sizes.
* Search terms are now shown in the subwindow title of the channel list.
* Added an option to toggle "illegal" channel name input. The new option is
  added to the "Advanced" page in the Settings dialog. This option is turned on
  by default.
* Bugfix: Using the /part command didn't work properly (or, at least, it didn't
  work how I wanted it to). The /part command has been completely re-written.
  Now, the "quit" message (if there is one) is passed to the subwindow and then
  closed directly.
* The /hide, /show, /maximize, /minimize, /restore, and /focus commands can now
  take hostIDs as their sole argument.
* Bugfix: fixed a bug where occasionally MERK would do a WHOIS on itself.
* Changes to the /print and /prints commands: they can now take server and
  window arguments like /hide and /show to target specific windows. If the
  server or window can't be found, the text is displayed to the current window.
* Changed the name of the $_HOST built-in alias to $_HOSTNAME.
* Added a new built-in alias: $_HOSTID, which contains the hostID of the server
  the window is connected to.
* Changed the "about" entry in the system tray menu: changed the icon to the
  application icon, and changed its title to "MERK IRC Client".
* Removed the "set channel modes" button.
* Right clicking on the "channel mode" display now displays a description of
  known channel modes for unprivleged users, or options to set channel modes
  for privleged users.
* Removed the "banned users" button from channel windows. The channel ban list
  is now a submenu of the "channel modes" right click menu.
* The channel ban list submenu is now "scrollable".
* Added an option to toggle the channel mode right click menu to the Settings
  dialog and the config command.
* New script-only command: random. This generates a random integer in a given
  range, and stores the integer in an alias.
* Bugfix: disabling aliases now properly throws an error if /alias or random
  are called in a script.
* Changed the command-line "banner" logo that appears when using the -h flag.
* Bugfix: changed how aliases are interpolated into input, whether in user
  input typed into the text input widget or in scripts. This should fix some
  bugs that might pop up when switching contexts, or using hotkeys.
* Removed the /s command shortcut for /script.
* Added a new built-in alias: $_WEB, which contains the URL of the MERK website.
* Bugfix: calling scripts/macros/etc with arguments that have ' in them will no
  longer crash the client on occasion.
* Bugfix: the previous bugfix broke the "if" script-only command. The bug has
  been fixed, and "if" is functional again.
* The "if" script-only command can now take a string as a value for any
  operator, including (eq), (ne), (lt), and (gt). For these operators, strings
  are measured for length, with the length being used.
* Bugfix: "goto" can now be used to jump to a line with a script-only command,
  and no longer throws an "unrecognized command" error when it does so.
* New script-only command: target. This creates a "target" that can be used
  with the "goto" command, making it safe to use goto in scripts that are
  inserted with the "insert" command. Targets cannot contain spaces, and must
  be unique in a given script.
* New subcommand for /window: fade. This allows for the transparency of the
  main application window to be set from 1% to 100%.

|==============================================================================|
|                              PLUGIN API CHANGES                              |
|==============================================================================|

* New Window class method: fade(). If called without arguments, it returns the
  percentage transparency of the subwindow. If called with an intger from 1 to
  100 as an argument, it sets the transparency of the subwindow.
* The Console method html() now converts IRC color and formatting codes into
  HTML for display.
* If the resize() Plugin inherited method is called without any arguments (or
  only one), the method will return a list of integers, containing the
  application window's width and height, in that order.
* New Plugin inherited method: location(). This returns a list containing the
  X and Y values of the location of the main application window.
* New Plugin inherited class method: fade(). If called without arguments, it
  returns the percentage transparency of the main application window. If called
  with an intger from 1 to 100 as an argument, it sets the transparency of the
  main application window.

|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|                                   0.051.550                                  |
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|

|==============================================================================|
|                              APPLICATION CHANGES                             |
|==============================================================================|

* The /window command now shows more subwindow information when called without
  any arguments.
* Removed the /subwindow command.
* Changed the /resize command to /size. It works exactly the same way, only if
  you call it without arguments, it displays the current subwindow's size.
* Changed the /move command. Call without arguments to see the current sub-
  window's coordinates.
* Bugfix: if multiple identical notification are sent to the systray, they are
  no longer duplicated.
* New option: trigger systray flash notifications on new channel chat. This
  option is enabled by default.
* New /window subcommand: calling /window layout without any arguments will
  generate a MERK script that recreate the current visible window layout. This
  command is disabled if scripting is disabled.
* Majorly revamped the Settings dialog.
* Changing the font in the Settings dialog now prompts the user to restart.
* Bugfix: certain QStyles no longer resize items in the "page selector" widget
  in the Settings dialog.
* Bugfix: the "page selector" in the Settings dialog will no longer have a
  border around it in any QStyle.
* Bugfix: pasting something into the text input widget now triggers the "come
  back from autoaway" event if that option is turned on.
* Bugfix: the text widget to input "realnames" in both the connection and the
  Settings dialog now block the input of control codes.
* Bugfix: the /delay command could cause a crashing error; it no longer does.
* Bugfix: error messages now follow the normal logging settings.
* More (hopefully all) server error messages are now shown to the user.
* Added an option to toggle whether server errror messages are displayed to the
  user in the current window, instead of just the server window. It's turned on
  by default.
* Added an option to en/disable the topic editor. The topic editor is enabled
  by default.
* Errors issued by the server are no longer ignored before registration.
* Moved the IRC color and markdown input into their own submenu in the Settings
  menu.
* Added a new icon for text input.
* The Log Manager has been re-written, and the option to "view" logs (that is,
  rendering the logs like chat) has been removed. The only option now is to
  export the logs like before.
* Added 'end' as a potential target to the 'goto' script-only command. This
  will immediately end a script. This can also be used in conjunction with the
  'if' script-only command.
* Added the day of the week to the "resumed" end-of-log-load message.
* Bugfix: using the /alias command with short values could result in the alias
  not being set properly.
* Bugfix: the "find" and "find and replace" dialogs in the script editor were
  broken. They function as intended now.
* Bugfix: scripts now can more reliably access the alias table, with values
  creating in script being updated more reliably.
* Bugfix: math expression parsing could return bad values on occasion.
* Bugfix: the "PASS :Not enough paramaters" error message that pops up during
  registration is no longer displayed to the user.
* Bugfix: aliases created in scripts are now "destroyed" as soon as the script
  exits. This "fixes" a bug where aliases were not being reliably updated in-
  between script runs.
* Bugfixes: global aliases cannot be "edited" in scripts. Aliases are only
  global if they are created from the text input widget.
* Resized the "status" icons in channel userlists. They are slightly smaller,
  and now actually scale with the app font size. The config file setting that
  set the "hard size" of icons for userlists has been removed.
* Added a "normal" user to the userlist display in the style editor. This can
  fit now that status icons are smaller.
* Added a new built-in alias: _LATEST, which contains a URL pointing to a
  directory containing the latest development builds of MERK.
* The base channel userlist width is no longer tied to the nickname padding
  length. By default, the width is the average width of 15 characters of the
  current font. This can be changed in the Settings dialog, the configuration
  file, or with the /config command.
* Added an option to open a server's connection script to the Windows menu.
  This option can be toggled in the Settings dialog or with the /config
  command.
* Bugfix: errors from automatically requested WHOIS errors (from the collecting
  of user hostmasks) are suppressed, and the nick is removed from the "request
  WHOIS" list in the IRC client.
* Bugfix: errors from attempting to register with a nickname that's already
  taken are suppressed, as MERK handles this situation automatically.
* Added an option to show ALL errors to the user, even those that are handled
  automatically.
* Bugfix: the "set away message" dialog now properly supports autocompleting
  shortcodes.
* Bugfix: the "find/find and replace" dialog in the Script and Python editor no
  longer creates an additional icon in the task bar, and is "always on top".
* Bugfix: the "find/find and replace" dialog will now use any selected text in
  the editor as the text to search for when the hotkeys are used.
* Bugfix: the "find/find and replace" dialog will now allow the user to select
  a new bit of text to perform a search by pressing the hotkey.
* Bugfix: the "find/find and replace" dialog no longer "flickers" when
  selecting a different bit of text to search for.
* Bugfix: triggering the "find/find and replace" dialog while the dialog is
  already open will automatically "switch" to the other type (that is, if the
  "find" dialog is open, and the "find and replace" hotkey is triggered, the
  "find" dialog will be replaced with the "find and replace" dialog). There is
  a flicker when this happens, due to how the dialog is built.
* Removed the "close" button from the "find/find and replace" dialog.
* The filename no longer appears in the "find/find and replace" dialog title,
  only the function of the dialog being currently displayed.
* Added a label to the "find/find and replace" dialog to show which window this
  dialog is "for". It displays the current base filename or host ID of the file
  being edited, or "Unknown" if the file doesn't have either of these.
* Added an option to set an image as the MDI area background to the Settings
  dialog.
* The MDI area background image can now be set via the /config command. The
  documentation has been updated for more information on how.
* Added additional sanity checks for the alias interpolation symbol and the
  "issue command" symbol to the /config command.
* Added a setting to control how the MDI background image gets displayed: it
  can either be scaled to the size of the workspace (the default), centered in
  the workspace, or tiled across the workspace. This new setting has been added
  to the Settings dialog, and can be changed with the /config command.
* Error messages for the /config command are now more descriptive; if there are
  only a set number of valid values for a given setting, they are displayed to
  the user in the error message.

|==============================================================================|
|                              PLUGIN API CHANGES                              |
|==============================================================================|

* Errors that are suppressed from view (due to settings) will no longer be
  passed to the error() plugin event. If these errors are set to be shown to
  the user, they will be passed to the error() event.

|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|                                   0.051.500                                  |
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|

|==============================================================================|
|                              APPLICATION CHANGES                             |
|==============================================================================|

* Bugfix: using "/window restart" under PyInstaller could crash the app.
* Added the ability to toggle "always on top" mode to the /window command.
* If "on-top" and "fullscreen" are enabled from the command-line, then they
  cannot be toggled with the /window command, the settings dialog, or the
  settings menu.
* When uninstalling a plugin with the plugin manager, if the plugin is open in
  the Python editor, the plugin manager will close the Python editor, without
  asking to save when the file is deleted. This behavior (enabled by default)
  can be togggled in the Python editor or with the /config command.
* ASCIImojis are now turned into shortcodes in the topic editor when editing a
  channel topic.
* In the plugin manager, if the script editor is disabled, the option to edit a
  plugin is still available in the right click context menu; the plugin source
  file will be opened in whatever default program the OS is set to use for
  Python source code files.
* Changed how a plugin's identifier is calculated. Now, a plugin' ID is stable
  across different application executions. Instead of a UUID, the plugin's ID
  is calculated from a MD5 hash of the plugins filename, module name, and the
  name of the plugin's class.
* Re-wrote and streamlined the plugin loading code.
* Bugfix: URLs surrounded by parenthesis are now detected and turned into links
  in chat.
* Bugfix: IRC color and formatting decoding to markup is now more accurate.
* Individual plugins can now be "paused" to temporarily prevent them from
  reacting to events or executing methods with /call.
* Added "play" and "pause" icons to the application for the GUI representation
  of "pausing" and "unpausing" plugins, respectively.
* Changed the "play notification sound" icon in the settings dialog to use the
  new "play" icon.
* Added a "subcommand" to the /window command, "pause", allowing scripts and
  hotkeys to pause and unpause plugins.
* The hotkey creation/editing dialog now includes macros and plugin /call
  commands as options.
* Added event code generators for pause() and unpause() to the Python editor.
* Added support for Wayland to the Linux binary distribution.
* Changed the size of the icons in the settings dialog page navigation panel,
  due to the fact that some Qt style themes could render the dialog unusable.
* Removed the option to select some specific Qt style themes due to the fact
  that they caused the application to crash.
* Bugfix: the settings dialog now reports what font the app is using more
  accurately.
* Markdown and IRC color markup are now no longer limited to text entered into
  the text input widget; they will be inserted into ANY message sent by MERK if
  they are turned on.
* Bugfix: markdown input was breaking using some command arguments. Now that
  markdown is turned on for messages only, commands should work properly again.
* Markdown and IRC color "markup" settings were moved to the "Miscellaneous"
  page of the settings dialog.
* Bugfix: toggling IRC color display no longer changes IRC colors in channel
  topics.
* Restored the IRC color display toggle to the settings menu.
* Changed how installed plugins are displayed in the "Tools" menu.
* Added an icon PNG file to the Linux binary and source distributions.
* Changed the "patrons" page in the about dialog.
* Tweaked the settings menu.
* Added a "tip of the day" dialog that displays on startup. This can be
  disabled in the Settings dialog or with a checkbox on the dialog itself.
* The "usage" script-only command can now check for one or more arguments,
  rather than a specific number.
* The default setting for "require exact number of arguments for usage" has
  been changed from "false" to "true".
* The GUI inputs for nicknames now blocks invalid nicknames for IRC. Nicknames
  can't start with numbers, or contain !, @, $, %, &, *, (, ), ., ,, /, ?, <,
  >, +, or =. These characters can't actually be entered into the input widget.
* The /nick command now also checks for nickname validity, and throws an error
  on invalid nicknames.
* Bugfix: larger font sizes "messed up" the Settings dialog display, rendering
  the dialog almost unusable. Font sizes in the Settings dialog are now limited
  to a maximum of 12pt. This can be changed either by editing the config file,
  or by using /config on maximum_font_size_for_settings_dialog.
* Using the /join command with an invalid channel name results in an error
  message. Channels in IRC cannot have commas or control codes.
* The channel join dialog now also prevents invalid characters from being used.
* New command: /subwindow displays size and location information about the
  current subwindow.
* Added a button to the Settings dialog to reset the application font back to
  the default.

|==============================================================================|
|                              PLUGIN API CHANGES                              |
|==============================================================================|

* Inherited methods markup() and unmarkup() can now insert or remove emoji and 
  ASCIImoji shortcodes.
* Bugfix: The uptime() event has been added to the plugin skeleton.
* Updated the plugin skeleton with better documentation.
* Added demojize() and deasciimojize() to the inherited plugin methods, which
  converts emojis and ASCIImojis in strings into shortcodes.
* Plugins no longer need to have unique NAME and VERSION attributes. Plugins
  with the same NAME and VERSION can be loaded at the same time.
* Changed the name of the master() and all_masters() plugin inherited methods
  to server_window() and all_servers(), respectively.
* Example plugins have been updated to use the new inherited method names.
* New plugin events: pause() (which is triggered when a plugin is paused), and
  unpause() (which is triggered when a plugin is unpaused).
* New Console class method: html(), which writes raw HTML to the console.

|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|                                   0.051.450                                  |
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|

|==============================================================================|
|                              APPLICATION CHANGES                             |
|==============================================================================|

* The settings dialog has been revamped.
* The plugin loading mechanism now tries to catch errors that arise while
  creating an instance of the plugin, and inform the user rather than crash the
  client.
* Bugfix: the plugin manager now reports the correct number of additional
  methods a plugin has.
* New feature: inject IRC colors into input. Both fore- and background colors
  can be set. <NUMBER to start a color block with only a foreground color, 
  or <NUMBER,NUMBER to start a color block with both foreground and background
  colors. Close color blocks with >. Just like with the markdown formatting
  injection feature, this can be turned off by the user.
* Color and markdown formatting input have been added to the documentation.
* Rewrote the "strip IRC color and formatting" algorithm to use some simple
  regexes rather than a bunch of replace() calls.
* Removed the ability to set/change the "erroneous nickname" setting from the
  settings dialog. The setting still exists, and can be changed by using the
  /config command or editing the configuration file.
* The text renderer now checks if text has a URL in it before trying to render
  URL links.
* Rewrote the text renderer's template and style system to make it a little
  more readable and efficient.
* New command: /browser, which opens a URL in the default browser.
* Tweak to the Python editor syntax highlighting; Plugin inherited methods now
  no longer need the 'self' identifier to be highlighted.
* Removed a now-unneeded dialog from the settings dialog.
* Bugfix: autoindentation in the Python editor no longer inserts extra levels
  of indentation occasionally.
* Bugfix: markdown input can now be escaped with \.
* Bugfix: markdown input no longer prevents link creation from some URLs.
* Added a link to the ASCIImoji website to the systray right-click menu, in the
  "Links" submenu.
* Added new built-in aliases: $_DLOGS, $_DPLUGINS, $_DSCRIPTS, $_DSETTTINGS,
  and $_DSTYLES. These contain the paths to each of MERK's different config/
  file directories.
* New command: /folder, which opens one or more paths in the default file
  manager.
* Added the option to disable the /browser command to the settings manager and
  the configuration file.
* Bugfix: when a connection fails or is lost, the client associated with that
  connection is now completely removed from the internal connection list.
* Bugfix: sudden disconnection from a server could cause a crash.
* Bugfix: if a reconnection fails without registration more than once, the user
  is notified about whether they want to keep attempting reconnects.
  Previously, this would result in a "spiral", where the client would keep
  trying to reconnect indefinitely. This behavior can be turned off in
  settings, if the user wants MERK to continue trying to connect without
  interruption.
* Bugfix: fixed the "Copy link location" entry in chat and server window
  context menus.
* The topic display in channel windows now displays IRC colors.
* Removed the option to toggle IRC colors from the settings menu. The toggle
  is now only in the settings dialog.
* Bugfix: the IRC color/formatting stripping code occasionally stripped commas
  from text. It no longer does.
* The channel topic is now shown in the tooltip of the topic editor. This
  behavior can be toggled in the settings dialog, on the channels page.
* Changed the behavior of the topic editor: clicking on the topic editor now
  moves the cursor to the end of the display instead of selecting the entire
  topic.
* Removed the option to display the channel topic in bold; channel topics in
  the topic display will now ONLY show in normal weight.
* Bugfix: the message renderer should detect just about all URLs and turn them
  into links if that option is enabled. Problems with links starting and ending
  with certain punctuation marks broke some links.
* Bugfix: IRC color code injection could strip < and > from input text.
* IRC color display in the channel topic editor can now be toggled in the
  settings dialog.
* Dark mode now has its own default text style that is separate from the light
  mode default style. When the user is in dark mode, editing that style will
  only change the default dark mode style, not the light mode style, and it
  will be loaded as the default in the style editor. The default dark mode text
  style filename is "dark.style".
* Changed the name of the default text style file to "light.style".
* Bugfix: the cursor will always be visible now when using the topic editor.
* Bugfix: occasionally, the topic editor would not be "enabled" (that is, allow
  the user to edit the topic) without switching to another subwindow.
* The dark mode text style is now clearly marked in the text style editor.
* Bugfix: restarting MERK from within the app no longer passes any user provided
  command-line arguments along to the new process. The -R,--run command-line
  argument is passed to the new process.
* Bugfix: servers are no longer saved to the connection history unless they
  have been connected to at least once. Occasionally, application arguments
  could have been saved as potential servers in user history in some edge
  cases.
* Bugfix: restarting MERK under PyInstaller on Linux now functions correctly.
* Bugfix: emoji shortcodes, ASCIImojis, and aliases are now injected into text
  entered into the topic editor.
* Bugfix: messages with IRC color codes in them were rendered in the same text
  style as a raw message; this no longer occurs, and appropriate text styles
  are now applied.
* Bugfix: WHOIS messages now have IRC color and formatting codes stripped from
  them.
* The topic editor now converts any topics on editing into a usable input
  format; for example, if iRC colors are enabled in the display, they will be
  converted into the IRC color input format. The same will happen with markdown
  and emoji shortcodes. IRC color and formatting input, and emojis are ALWAYS
  enabled on topics. ASCIImojis are not turned into ASCIImoji shortcodes, and
  are just left in the topic text.
* Activating a server, channel, or private chat subwindow sets focus on the
  text input widget immediately, instead of being slightly delayed.
* The /fullscreen command has been removed, and had its functionality added to
  the /window command.
* Bugfix: text is now selectable in the topic editor.
* Bugfix: fixed a crashing bug with selecting log saving intervals.
* Added MansionNET to the internal network link list.

|==============================================================================|
|                              PLUGIN API CHANGES                              |
|==============================================================================|

* Bugfix: alias interpolation is handled before shortcode injection in inherited
  messaging methods due to sometimes unexpected behavior.
* New inherited method: color(), which takes a string with MERK IRC color tags
  and returns a string with the appropriate IRC color codes inserted into it.
* New inherited method: markdown(), which takes a string with MERK markdown
  formatting and returns a string with the appropriate IRC formatting codes
  inserted into it.
* New inherited method: strip(), which strips all IRC color and formatting
  codes from a string and returns the result.
* New inherited method: colored(), which returns True if a string contains IRC
  color/formatting codes, and False if not.
* New inherited method: browser(), which opens a URL in the default browser.
* New inherited method: folder(), which opens a directory in the default file
  manager.
* New inherited method: current(), which returns a MERK Window object for the
  currently active chat window, or None if the currently active window is not a
  chat window.
* New plugin event: uptime(), which triggers once a second for every server,
  channel, or private chat window while they are connected to a server.
* New inherited method: uncolor(), which takes a string and converts any IRC
  color codes in it into the same "markup" used by the IRC color input feature.
* New inherited method: unmarkdown(), which takes a string and converts any
  IRC text formatting codes in it and converts it into the same flavor of
  markdown used in the markdown input feature.
* New inherited method: markup(), which takes a string with IRC color and
  formatting "markup" (like that used with IRC color and formatting input)
  and converts it into IRC color and formatting codes.
* New inherited method: unmarkup(), which takes a string with IRC color and
  formatting codes, and turns it into formatting "markup", like that used with
  IRC color and markdown input.

|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|                                   0.051.400                                  |
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|

|==============================================================================|
|                              APPLICATION CHANGES                             |
|==============================================================================|

* Bugfix: script filename autocomplete worked even if scripting was
  disabled.
* Changed the name of the configuration file setting for autocompleting file-
  names for /edit, /script, and /python commands to "autocomplete_filenames"
  to reflect its current usage.
* Bugfix: user information was being saved *while* checking for its
  validity in the connection dialog.
* Changed how the connection history is written. Now, connections are only
  written to the history in the user config file when a connection has been
  successfully completed (that is, registration has finished successfully).
* Connection history now respects the "--donotsave" command-line flag.
* "--donotsave" only sets the default for the connection dialog. If the option
  to save to the user config is turned on in the connection dialog, that will
  be the new default while the app is running. This option is not saved to the
  config file.
* New option: toggle saving connection history to the user file.
* Bugfix: in the log manager, doing a search from the tab bar now switches
  to the log viewer tab when activated.
* Added a setting to the config file that sets the "name" of networks on IRC
  servers that aren't on a network; by default, this is set to "Unknown".
  This setting is not settable in the settings dialog, but can be changed with
  the /config command or by editing the config file manually.
* Bugfix: removed a duplicate call to QApplication() from merk.py. This was
  preventing the initial connection dialog from being shown on some 32-bit
  Linux installs.
* Tweak to merk.py to show the proper executable name in the --help display,
  depending on platform.
* All windows associated with a given connection are hidden before closing when
  that connection is disconnected.
* The windowbar now correctly hides windows for connections in the process of
  disconnecting.
* New option: display channel topic in the tooltip for channel entries in the
  windowbar. Disabled by default.
* Bugfix: the application title will now no longer change for subwindows that
  are not visible or are in the process of disconnecting from the server. The
  application title will show the "default" window title in both of those
  cases.
* Bugfix: fixed the application title not correctly updating when switching
  from editing a connection script to a user script.
* Changed the internal and config file name of the "display active subwindow
  in application title" setting to reflect how the setting actually works.
* ALL script error messages now show the name of the file the error occurred
  in, not just errors in script-only commands. If the error occurred in a
  connection script, the filename is set to SERVER:PORT, and if the filename
  is not known or does not exist, it is set to 'script'. The base filename of
  the script is used (without the path).
* Added a setting to toggle re-execution of plugin init() events on plugin
  reload.
* The default setting to auto-reload plugins on Python editor close has been
  changed from "true" to "false". Users can still change this setting. The
  name for this setting has been changed in the configuration file to make
  sure that this setting is changed for all users going forward.
* Clicking "apply" on the settings dialog no longer reloads plugins.
* Bugfix: an error encountered while loading plugins stop any plugins from
  loading. Plugin load errors are now handled properly, and any plugins NOT
  showing errors will load fully.
* Added a setting to toggle whether plugins are automatically reloaded when a
  plugin is uninstalled with the plugin manager.
* New command: /unmacro, which removes macros from memory.
* Bugfix: the "bold on hover" effect no longer "gets stuck" on the menu- and
  windowbar.
* Updated icons in the "Insert" menu in the Python editor.
* Bugfix: fixed errors with the /macro command's error reporting.
* Bugfix: the plugin manager could throw an error when trying to update a
  plugin console while it's open.
* Bugfix: the plugin console identifier in the plugin manager was not being
  set from the config file properly.
* The "icon" emoji that is used to signify a plugin's console is open in the
  plugin manager was changed to one that is more universal across platforms.
* Added an option (disabled by default) to show a plugin's console as soon as
  it is created for the first time.
* Added an option to the plugin manager to show/hide plugin consoles to the
  right click menu on plugin entries.
* Bugfix: plugin consoles would not be able to be shown from the plugin manager
  right click menu when the Python editor was disabled. This no longer occurs.
* Bugfix: mIRC colors now work properly, and "close" text formatting properly.
* Bugfix: disconnecting from all servers closed or hid ALL subwindows, even
  those not involved with network activity.
* Moved the cursor settings from the "Input" section of the settings dialog to
  the "Miscellaneous" section of the dialog.
* New feature: use markdown to format input text. Supported markdown "tags" are
  italic, bold, strikethrough, and underline. Only displayed in the client if
  IRC colors are turned on, but the messages will be sent to the server with
  the formatting codes.
* Added "use markdown in input" option to the settings menu and the settings
  dialog.
* Added some of the new settings to the settings menu and windowbar context
  menu.
* New command: /_trace, which executes a TRACE command on the server. This
  command is usually limited to IRCops. All command output is displayed in the
  server window for the server the command was issued on.
* Bugfix: Underscores in command names are now ignored for the purpose of
  sorting the command list with the /help command display. Previously, all the
  commands that started with an underscore were displayed at the very top of
  the command list; all commands are now in alphabetical order, while ignoring
  the underscores in the name of the command.
* Bugfix: /quitall ignored the quit message passed to it in some circumstances.
* Added ASCIImoji (https://asciimoji.com/) support! ASCIImoji shortcodes are in
  the format (text). Autocomplete, syntax highlighting in the text input
  widget, and inserting ASCIImoji shortcodes every place that emoji shortcodes
  could go is supported. Settings specific for emojis have now, in many cases,
  been changed to support both emoji and ASCIImoji shortcodes. Both emoji and
  ASCIImoji shortcodes can be en/disabled separately; one can be used without
  the other. Autocomplete in the settings dialog for away and quit messages has
  been updated to use both types of *mojis.
* Much of the formatting of the settings dialog has been updated.
* The emoji that is used in the plugin manager to show that a plugin's console
  is open or in use can now use an ASCIImoji, instead.
* Changed the URL "detector" in the to be a bit more permissive in the types of
  URLs it detects.
* Bugfix: the link creator in the text renderer now properly creates links that
  might contain leading or trailing punctuation.
* Changed the default quit and away messages to use built-in aliases. The name
  of each setting has been changed in the configuration file so that newer
  installs use the new version.
* Bugfix: if servers did not have a network, channel or private chat subwindows
  could not be created. This has been fixed; the network is now set to the
  default unknown network name (which is "Unknown"). This can be changed in the
  config file or with the /config command.
* Bugfix: autocomplete is now much more forgiving, and will detect (and
  trigger) on input with mixed cases, which it wasn't doing before.
* Bugfix: calling /window without proper arguments both printed an error
  message AND sent the improper line as a message to the current chat. This no
  longer happens.
* Bugfix: "/window uninstall" (called without arguments) now lists the
  installed plugins by both name, version, and filename. The previous display
  only displayed plugins by filename, and incorrectly at that.
* Calling "/window install" (without any other arguments) now displays a usage
  error instead of listing all installed plugins.
* Bugfix: If the "reload after uninstall" setting is turned off, an uninstalled
  plugin is now completely removed from memory without reloading the list, and
  if the plugin manager is opened, the plugin list display is refreshed. Both
  the unload() and uninstall() events are triggered before removal, in that
  order.

|==============================================================================|
|                              PLUGIN API CHANGES                              |
|==============================================================================|

* Plugins are now completely removed from memory before being reloaded. This
  behavior can be toggled in the settings dialog, but is turned on by default.
* Plugin init() events are now executed EVERY TIME a plugin is loaded or
  reloaded. The documentation and the plugin skeleton have been updated to
  note this change.
* Re-execution of init() events can be turned off in settings or with the
  /config command.
* New plugin inherited method: unmacro(), which removes a macro from memory,
  much like the /unmacro command.
* New plugin event: uninstall(), which is triggered when the plugin manager or
  the "/window uninstall" command is used to uninstall a plugin. This event
  will NOT be triggered if the plugin is uninstalled via command-line flag.
* The example plugins in the repo have been updated to use the uninstall()
  event.
* New plugin event: unload(), which is triggered when the plugin is unloaded.
  This event is triggered every time the plugin is unloaded, including when
  the plugin list is reloaded (each plugin is unloaded, and then reloaded).
* New plugin inherited method: asciimojize(), which inserts ASCIImojis into
  text with shortcodes.
* Bugfix: plugins can now contain classes that do NOT inherit from Plugin; they
  will not be loaded into memory as a plugin, but can be used by plugins.
* The "window" argument is no longer passed to the "joined" event. Due to a
  race condition, this could cause errors to trigger in certain circumstances.
  The channel's window can still be obtained with the channel() inherited
  method.
* New Plugin inherited methods: connect() (which connects MERK to an IRC server
  WITHOUT executing any existing connection scripts) and xconnect() (which
  connects MERK to an IRC server AND executes any existing connection scripts).

|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|                                   0.051.350                                  |
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|

|==============================================================================|
|                              APPLICATION CHANGES                             |
|==============================================================================|

* Fixed a "bug" that caused versions of Python lower than 3.11 (I think) to be
  unable to execute merk.py
* Fixed a bug in the Linux PyInstaller version of the app: the "Directories"
  subdirectory in the "Tools" menu would not open the desired directory in the
  default file manager on this platform; the Python version of the app could
  open these directories in the default file manager, but not the Pyinstaller
  version. This is fixed.
* Added a command-line option to install plugins. Plugins must be ZIP files or
  Python modules, and only Python modules and PNG files will be extracted into
  the plugins directory; MERK script will be extracted into the scripts
  directory. If a Python module is installed, if the icon is in the same 
  directory as the module, it will be installed along with the module. Plugins
  installed with this method will ALWAYS overwrite existing files in the
  plugins or scripts directory.
* The --uninstall-all command-line option has been removed, and replaced with
  the --uninstall option. Call --uninstall without any arguments to see a list
  of installed plugin filenames, pass a filename as an argument to uninstall
  the plugin (and icon), and pass 'all' as an argument to uninstall all plugins.
* Cleaned up some of the HTML in README.html
* New command-line option: --enable-plugins (-E). This enables plugins. If both
  --enable-plugins and --disable-plugins are issued at the same time, an error
  is shown, and MERK will not start.
* Enabling or disabling plugins on the command-line will ALWAYS save to the
  config file, even if --donotsave is enabled. This fixes a bug where if you
  enabled or disabled plugins, and chose not to save settings, plugins would
  not actually be enabled or disabled.
* Logs are now saved in ONLY lowercase letters in the filename.
* Added the "erroneous nickname" default to the settings dialog.
* Removed the option to convert channel names to "links" to channels in chat.
  This was really slowing down chat rendering, and honestly, didn't seem to
  be of much use.
* Moved the option to turn the /call command on and off to the scripting page
  in the Settings dialog.
* Fixed a bug with disabling the /user command in the Settings dialog.
* Shrunk the width of the input options button on chat windows, and fixed a
  bug where the input options button could gain focus.
* Fixed a bug where some non-interactable elements of chat windows could gain
  focus.
* Added two new subcommands to the /windows command: install and uninstall,
  which install and uninstall plugins, respectively. The "install" subcommand
  will NOT overwrite files unless that option is turned on.
* The help menu is now "manually" closed after clicking on the document entries
  in the menu.
* New command: /python, which opens the Python editor. The command is disabled
  if the plugins or the Python editor is disabled.
* Fixed a bug where the Python editor could be opened even if the editor was
  disabled, by clicking on a plugin in the "Tools" menu.
* Fixed a bug where the full height of entries in the menubar was not shown in
  the gui. The menubar's height has now been slightly increased, as has the
  "button" menu entry points.
* The windowbar now has the same height as the menubar.
* The log manager can now be launched from the systray menu for servers that
  don't belong to a network.
* The Python editor's window icon is now the Python icon.
* Changed the Python icon to something more modern.
* Added a windowbar option: flash entry on unread nickname mentions. This is
  turned off by default, and can be set independently of the "flash on unread
  messages" option.
* If "autocomplete script filenames" is turned on, this will now work with
  the /python command for Python plugin files.
* If both the Python editor and the plugin manager are open, the plugin manager
  will reload plugins when the Python editor is closed, but only if the current
  file has been saved. This behavior is turned on by default, but can be turned
  off by the user in the "File" menu. The setting is saved to the config file.
  Plugins will only be reloaded if the saved Python file is in the plugins
  directory, and only if the saved file has the ".py" file extension.
* Plugin events are now wrapped in "try" calls to prevent plugins from crashing
  the client.
* Plugin event execution errors are now displayed in a message box to the user.
  This can be toggled in the settings dialog.
* The "event generators" in the Python editor menu now also create local
  variables for the values passed to the event methods.
* Fixed a bug where scripts execution would halt on script-only command errors,
  regardless if "halt on execution" was turned off.
* Fixed a bug where the "halt" script-only command would not actually halt a
  script if "halt script on error" was turned off.
* Fixed a bug where some entries in the "Help" menu would crash MERK if the
  program was being ran from a directory that was NOT the program installation
  directory.
* Added a server identifier to the "script"  tab in the connection dialog, if
  simplified dialogs are turned on.
* Cleaned up the connection dialog. The tab "labels" (that appeared at the top
  of the tab contents) have been removed, and the spacing of the widgets in the
  layout has been tweaked.
* Drag-and-drop has been added to the main application. Users can drag MERK
  scripts or Python scripts onto the main application window to open up those
  files in editors.
* Plugin ZIP files can now be dragged-and-dropped onto the main application
  window to install them.
* Drag-and-drop can now be turned off in the settings dialog.
* The /help command now shows what "subcommands" for the /window command are
  currently enabled.
* Tweaked the /help command display to fix some typos and formatting errors.
* Added an option (which is turned on by default) that places hotkey, ignore,
  and plugin managers on top of the main window.
* Removed the colons (:) from the text input lables on the connect dialog.
* Scripting threads now have their main execution loop wrapped in a try/except
  statement. Scripts could sometimes exit pre-maturely, and would take down
  the client with it; this should no longer occur.
* Error messages encountered while executing individual lines in scripts should
  be more informative.
* Exiting MERK on Linux no longer causes a segmentation fault/core dump. I'm
  still not exactly sure why this was occuring (I'm assuming because of the
  multi-threaded nature of various features); os._exit() is now used to
  terminate the application upon exit.
* Scripting threads are now closed "properly" before being deleted. This was
  causing race-condition crashing in certain circumstances. The timeout for the
  thread closing is set by default to 1000ms, but can be changed in the config
  file.
* Re-worked the layout of the settings dialog to be more compact.
* New setting: write all script errors to STDOUT. This setting is turned off
  by default, and can be toggled on the "advanced" page in the settings dialog.

|==============================================================================|
|                              PLUGIN API CHANGES                              |
|==============================================================================|

* Plugins no longer have to have an event method to be loaded without errors;
  they can have methods executable with the /call command without any event
  methods.
* The "joined" event is now slightly delayed until the channel's userlist is
  fully populated.
* The Twisted client that triggered the event is now passed to the "joined"
  event as an argument.
* Plugin load and refresh mechanism has been streamlined, making loading and
  reloading the full plugin list slightly faster.

