|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|                                   0.051.300                                  |
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|

|==============================================================================|
|                              APPLICATION CHANGES                             |
|==============================================================================|

* Fixed a bug with MERK exiting cleanly when using the /exit command.
* Changed the layout of the "Logs" and "Plugins" sections of the Settings
  dialog.
* Fixed some of the text on the "Input" section of the Settings dialog.
* Fixed a bug with autoindent in the Python editor.
* The tab key in the Python editor is now overridden if autoindent is turned
  on, and inserts the default indent when pressed.
* The Plugin Manager now generates a README file for exported plugin zips.
* The Plugin Manager now prompts for an icon on export, if the plugin doesn't
  already have one. Selecting an icon is not mandatory for export.
* Added a Linux binary distribution.
* Fixed a bug for IRCds without a "network" attribute set.
* Removed some of the decoration from the systray context menu. It wasn't
  rendering at all under Linux, and honestly, didn't really do much of anything
  except look a little pretty.
* Completely re-wrote the build system for both Windows and Linux.
* Scripting no longer has multi-line comments; they were not very useful, and
  actively interfered with some script-only commands like goto. Now, scripts
  can only comment by using the /rem command.
* Removed the /reclaim command. This functionality can be implemented with
  plugins, now, and do not require a separate, threaded command.
* Removed the /shell command. This functionality can also be implemented with
  plugins (and honestly implemented better).
* Removed the /random command. Again, this can be better implemented with a
  plugin.
* New command: /admin. This requests (and displays) administrative information
  from an IRC server.
* Commands that can only be used by server operators will start with an under-
  score. This is to prevent users from "accidentally" using or autocompleting
  the command, and to distinguish them from normal commands.
* New command: /_die. This tells the server to shut down, and can only be issued
  by server operators.
* New command: /_connect. This tells the server (or another server) to connect
  to a server. Can only be issued by server operators.
* New command: /info. This requests server information from the server.
* New command: /ison. This displays if the nicknames passed to it are currently
  online.
* New command: /_kill. This forcibly removes a client from the IRC network,
  and can only be issued by IRC operators.
* New command: /links. This requests a list of the servers the IRC server is
  connected to.
* New command: /lusers. This requests statistics about the server.
* New command: /_rehash. This causes the server to reprocess and reload
  configuration files, and can only be issued by IRC operators.
* Renamed the /raw command to /quote, to match other IRC clients.
* Added an option to toggle showing LUSERS responses in the current window;
  by default, it is turned off, and will only display in the server window.
* Added an option to toggle showing ISON responses in the current window;
  by default, it is turned off, and will only display in the server window.
* Major bugfix: users can no longer "drag" the view in the input widget, thus
  hiding the text in the input widget. The text input widget will always show
  the single line of input text now, regardless of whether the users drags the
  mouse inside of the widget. This bugfix has also been applied to the text
  entry widgets for the default quit message and default away message in the
  settings dialog.
* Removed the "close" button from the log manager.
* Moved some of the "single line" management code for the text input widget
  into the widget class itself.
* Fixed a bug that only seemed to occur in the Linux Python (non-PyInstaller)
  version of the app: when all visible subwindows were closed, the app would
  hang on closing the last window. This no longer occurs, in any version.
* New command: /wallops. This sends a message to all operators.
* New command: /userhost. This requests information about users from the
  server.
* Moved MansionNET into its proper place in the server list.
* Fixed a bug where there was no fallback nickname if the nickname trying
  to be set failed the server's rules. The fallback nickname ("Guest") is now
  set in the configuration file, under "bad_nickname_fallback".
* Changed how nick collisions are handled: if an alternate nick is not provided
  or is also in use, a random number from between 1 and 999 is selected and
  appended to the nickname and tried. Previously, the random number would be
  from 1 to 99.

|==============================================================================|
|                              PLUGIN API CHANGES                              |
|==============================================================================|

* The Window nicks() method no longer returns None.
* The Window users() method no longer returns None.
* Changes to the Window users() method: now, if a string containing a channel
  status is passed as an argument, a list of users in the channel with that
  status is returned, with an empty list being returned if there are no users
  with that status.
* New plugin event: ison(). This triggers when a response to the ISON command
  is received.
* Fixed a bug with the closed() plugin event; the event no longer fires with
  the name of *every* existing window whenever a window closes.

