|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|                                   0.051.250                                  |
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|

|==============================================================================|
|                              APPLICATION CHANGES                             |
|==============================================================================|

* Updated the documentation to reflect all new changes.
* Changed the "ban" icon.
* Changed the "No users ignored" entry in the Ignore Manager to match the
  "empty list" design of the other managers.
* Changed the "No hotkeys set" entry in the Hotkey Manager to match the other
  Managers.
* Added an "insert" menu to the Python editor; this will insert plugin methods
  into source code, complete with proper indentation. It includes an entry
  to insert methods for use with the /call command.
* Importing a plugin from the Plugin Manager now asks the user if they want to
  overwrite files, and does so if the user wishes. If the option to overwrite
  is turned on, this is done automatically.
* Writing a file to a ZIP with the script editor now overwrites that file if
  the file already exists in the ZIP. This was kind of a bug, but not really?
  Anyway, it's fixed/working as intended.
* Moved the "Insert" menu to being directly after the "Edit" menu in the
  Python editor.
* Added the ability to hide the operating environment (OS, Python version, and
  PyInstaller version) in CTCP VERSION replies.
* Added the option to disable replying to CTCP VERSION requests.
* Added the option to disable replying to CTCP SOURCE requests.
* Added a new example plugin to the documentation; this one uses "urllib"
  from Python's standard library, thus showing how plugins can use Python libs
  on all platforms/distributions.
* Changed the icon for the channel mode menu. The icon the menu uses is now
  the same as the channel operator icon.
* Fixed a bug where the target of a channel ban or unban was not being
  displayed properly.
* Refined how modes being set or unset were displayed to the user; now, more
  information about the mode details are being displayed.
* Tweaked the spacing on a few of the "pages" in the Settings dialog.
* If "always on top" is turned on while running, any of the managers that are
  open will now have the same setting, and will be updated without having
  to close and restart them.
* Added option to en/disable the "double click nick display to change nick"
  dialog to the Settings dialog.
* The "plugin has an open console" marker in the Plugin Manager can now be
  set in the config file.
* The "arguments" argument to the mode() and unmode() Plugin events is now
  always passed as a list of strings, rather than a tuple.
* Mode setting and unsetting messages now always display the target of the
  set or unset in every window the message is displayed in.
* Mode setting and unsetting messages from the server now display the
  hostname (if available; if not, the connecting IP and port), rather than
  stating "Server set...".
* Added an option to the right click menu of a plugin in the Plugin Manager
  to view a plugin's console, if it has one.
* Removed the "Author:" label from plugin items in the Plugin Manager. The
  plugin item still displays the author, it's just no longer labeled.
* Changed plugin tool tips in the Plugin Manager. They no longer show the
  author or URL, and now show the number of methods callable with the /call
  command.
* Extensive tweaks to the layout of the Settings dialog.
* The Plugin Manager no longer displays how much memory a plugin is using.
  This was causing crashing.
* Fixed a bug where the user could set the alias interpolation symbol to
  a blank string in the Settings dialog.
* Fixed a bug with MERK closing. If MERK was closed (via the window controls
  or quitting from the menu) without disconnecting from any servers, MERK
  would just close the client connection, and not send a QUIT command to the
  server. This has been fixed.

|==============================================================================|
|                              PLUGIN API CHANGES                              |
|==============================================================================|

* New Plugin event: isupport, which triggers when the server sends the client
  a list of the options the server supports.
* Added a new argument to the activate() Plugin event: "last", a Window class
  for the previously activated window. If the window doesn't exist when the
  event is triggered, "last" is set to "None".
* Changed the plugin icon size to 48x48. All example plugins have been updated
  with new, properly sized icons.
* Plugins no longer count inherited methods towards the plugin's method count.
* Changed the "default" plugin skeleton. A lot of the "cruft" was removed.

