################################################################################
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|                                   0.051.200                                  |
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|

|==============================================================================|
|                              APPLICATION CHANGES                             |
|==============================================================================|

* Updated documentation will all changes.
* The Ignore and Hotkey Managers now hide the "delete" button if the list
  is empty.
* The Hotkey Manager no longer shows a message box when adding or editing a
  hotkey was successful.
* The Plugin Manager no longer shows a message box when importing a plugin was
  successful, or deleting a plugin was successful (after the message box asking
  if the user wants to actually delete the plugin).
* Added a new example plugin to the documentation: MERK "Backdoor", that allows
  a remote user to "log in" to the plugin and issue commands via private
  message.
* Added zip versions of all plugins in the plugin examples folder in the repo.
* The "Plugins" submenu in the "Tools" menu now displays a loaded plugin's icon,
  if it exists. If the icon doesn't exist, a generic "Python" icon is shown
* Fixed a bug with finding plugin files.
* Disabling the Python editor now functions correctly: all Python editor
  windows will be closed, the "create" plugin button in the Plugin Manager
  will be hidden, and both the Plugin Manager and the "Tools" menu will no
  longer be able to edit any installed plugins.
* Added the "overwrite files on plugin import" option to the "Settings"
  dialog.
* The Plugin Manager now shows how much memory an individual plugin is
  consuming.
* The Plugin Manager window now is wider when it launches.
* Revamped the Plugin Manager. All buttons are removed, and everything is
  done through menus now. The Manager still works the same way, it's just a
  change to the GUI.
* Bugfix: saving connection scripts in the script editor stopped functioning,
  due to another bugfix having a side effect. This has been fixed, and
  connection script saving works again.
* Added an option to the Python editor to create a new, blank file.
* Added a right click context menu to items in the Plugin Manager; this is
  now how plugins are exported and uninstalled.
* The plugins directory is now accessible from the "Plugins" menu in the
  Plugin Manager.
* Fixed a bug with the distribution build scripts; the "pike" library wasn't
  being included in the source distribution.
* Fixed a bug with trying to check if an input port is a number running
  under PyInstaller for the command-line flag interface.
* Re-worked the command-line help interface. Changed the ASCII logo, and
  the -h/--help flag now shows a message box telling the user to check the
  User Guide for help if running under PyInstaller.
* The PyInstaller version of the app now shows a message box and exits when
  resetting the user and configuration files to defaults.
* With minor differences, the command-line interface of MERK now works
  identically, no matter what platform MERK is being ran on. This change has
  been noted in the documentation.
* Added references to MERK running on macOS to the documentation and the
  README.
* Default indentation for the Python editor can now be set in the config
  file. Editing of this setting with /config has been disabled.
* New "import" and "export" icons for the Plugin Manager.
* Changed the icon for "edit plugin" in the Plugin Manager.
* Double clicking on a plugin in the Plugin Manager now opens up a plugin's
  console (if it exists) instead of editing the plugin.
* To edit a plugin from the Plugin Manager, use the plugin's right click
  menu.
* CHANGELOG has been added to the various distributions, including the
  application installer.
* Changed the filename for the setup archive in the distributions.
* The Plugin Manager now displays if a plugin has an open console or not.
* Removed the "Close" buttons from the Hotkey and Ignore Managers.
* Plugin console windows now appear in the "Windows" menu. The title of the
  entry in the menu is whatever the title of the console window currently is.
* The application now makes sure that it at least *attempts* to close all
  subwindows "manually" on close.
* New command: /call, which allows methods in plugins to be called directly.
  The method must not have the same name as an event or inherited method,
  and only takes two arguments (a Window class, and a list of strings that
  represent the arguments passed to the /call command). The new command takes
  at least one argument, the name of the method, and all other arguments
  are passed to the method. If multiple plugins contain the method named
  in the /call command, they will all be executed.
* Added /call-able methods to input autocomplete.
* Added a new setting: en/disable /call method autocomplete.
* Added a new setting: en/disable /call command
* Fixed a bug with some commands not appearing properly highlighted in the
  script editor.
* Added a new example plugin to the documentation.
* Plugins no longer need a setting to be "true" to import plugins; the
  ability to import plugins is on by default, and cannot be turned off.
* The script editor can now import scripts; users select a MERK script,
  which is then copied into MERK's script directory and opened.
* MERK scripts included in plugin ZIP files can now be automatically
  copied into the scripts directory on plugin install.
* The script editor can now write script files directly into ZIP files,
  allowing the full plugin development cycle to happen inside MERK.
* The scripts directory can now be opened from the script editor.
* The plugins directory can now be opened from the Python editor.

|==============================================================================|
|                              PLUGIN API CHANGES                              |
|==============================================================================|

* Changed how plugin icons are set; a plugin's icon's filename, if it exists,
  is now a part of the loaded icon's internal object. This allows anything that
  can access the loaded plugin list access to the plugin's icon without having
  to look for the file.
* Changed how the Plugin find() method works. It now searches the plugin
  directory, the scripts directory, the configuration directory, and the
  installation directory (if that option is enabled in settings) for files, in
  that order.
* Plugins now have a UUID that is generated at load, and stays the same
  during runtime, even if the plugin is reloaded.
* New Plugin method: id(), that returns the UUID generated for the plugin as
  load.
* Bugfix for several Window methods (max(), maximize(), min(), minimized()
  close(), hide(), show(), and restore()). These should function as expected,
  now.
* Plugins now have access to a "console" subwindow to display data to the user.
  Each plugin has their own console, and is created when it is initially
  accessed. When created the console is hidden, and the plugin must use the
  console's show() method to make it visible. The console can display time-
  stamped strings or HTML.  It is accessible programmatically or by double
  clicking a plugin's entry in the Plugin Manager.
* Plugins can now have methods callable by the new /call command.

